article.story: HOUSTON -- — Nick Caldwell had 26 points, Roger McFarlane scored 20 and Southeastern Louisiana rolled to an 80-58 victory over Houston Christian on Monday night. Caldwell added five rebounds for the Lions (8-13, 3-5 Southland Conference). McFarlane hit two 3-pointers and grabbed seven rebounds. Roscoe Eastmond had 13 points and went 5 for 10 from the floor. Bonke Maring finished with 14 points for the Huskies (5-14, 3-5). Dominic Capriotti added 12 points and Marcus Greene scored 11. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
